{
  "text": "In accordance with our recent data, a significant increase in the mitochondrial membrane fluidity was observed in the hearts exposed to STZ-DM ( Fig. 1 ) [CITATION_1] , Waczul\u00edkov\u00e1 et al. 2007 ). An elevated formation of mPTP could be one of the possible explanations of the observed mitochondrial membrane fluidization. Enhanced formation and a short-term mPTP opening observed during the acute STZ-DM resulted in mitochondrial membrane fluidization and facilitation of ATP transport without lethal damage [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "10245459",
